-- Discount Investment Drops Most in 3 Weeks on Koor Stake Buy Plan
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-04-08T08:29:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-08/discount-investment-drops-most-in-3-weeks-on-koor-stake-buy-plan.html
Discount Investment Corp. (DISI)  fell to
the lowest level in more than three weeks as the holding company
plans to invest 800 million shekels ($214 million) in cash and
the rest in shares for full ownership of Koor Industries Ltd.  Discount Investment, which owns 70.11  percent of Koor 
according to data compiled by Bloomberg,  declined  3.2 percent to
19.56 shekels, the lowest intraday level since March 15, at
11:06 a.m. in Tel Aviv. Koor fell 0.3 percent to 60.11 shekels.  Israeli billionaire Nochi Dankner holds a stake in Discount
Investment via his holdings in  IDB Holding Corp. (IDBH)  IDB Holding,
which owns stakes in both companies via its IDB Development
Corp., dropped 0.6 percent to 29.20 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in  Tel Aviv  at 
